{
  "analysis": "We are at the root directory /app. Likely the kernel source is at /app/linux-6.9 as indicated in the command. Need to create an initramfs that will allow booting into the kernel with a root login. We need to create a minimal root filesystem with init script, busybox, and necessary devices. Let's first explore the directory to see what's available.",
  "plan": "1. List files in /app to see existing directories. 2. Check if busybox is installed or we need to build it. 3. Create a directory for ramfs (e.g., /app/ramfs) and build a minimal root filesystem with init script that spawns a shell. 4. Use cpio and gzip to create initramfs.cpio.gz. 5. Test with qemu command.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "ls -la\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "which busybox\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "mkdir -p /app/ramfs\n",
      "duration": 0.1
